{"parse":{"title":"Bloody Sunday: Scenes from the Saville Inquiry","pageid":21593281,"revid":791720048,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\">For other uses, see <a href=\"/wiki/Bloody_Sunday_(disambiguation)\" class=\"mw-redirect mw-disambig\" title=\"Bloody Sunday (disambiguation)\">Bloody Sunday</a>.</div>\n<table class=\"infobox vevent\" style=\"width:22em\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" class=\"summary\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-style: italic\">Bloody Sunday: Scenes from the Saville Inquiry</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:Bloody_Sunday_(play).jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Bloody Sunday (play).jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/c/c0/Bloody_Sunday_%28play%29.jpg/220px-Bloody_Sunday_%28play%29.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"357\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/c/c0/Bloody_Sunday_%28play%29.jpg 1.5x\" data-file-width=\"248\" data-file-height=\"402\" /></a><div>Oberon Books first edition cover</div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"white-space: nowrap\">Written by</th><td class=\"description\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/Richard_Norton-Taylor\" title=\"Richard Norton-Taylor\">Richard Norton-Taylor</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"white-space: nowrap\">Date premiered</th><td>\n7 April 2005</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"white-space: nowrap\">Place premiered</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Tricycle_Theatre\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Tricycle Theatre\">Tricycle Theatre</a><br />London</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"white-space: nowrap\">Original language</th><td>\nEnglish</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"white-space: nowrap\">Subject</th><td>\nA dramatisation of the hearings of evidence given of the 1972 violence in Derry, Northern Ireland.</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"white-space: nowrap\">Genre</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Drama\" title=\"Drama\">Drama</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><i><b>Bloody Sunday: Scenes from the Saville Inquiry</b></i> is a 2005 dramatisation by English journalist <a href=\"/wiki/Richard_Norton-Taylor\" title=\"Richard Norton-Taylor\">Richard Norton-Taylor</a> of four years of evidence of the <a href=\"/wiki/Bloody_Sunday_Inquiry\" title=\"Bloody Sunday Inquiry\">Saville Inquiry</a>, distilled into two hours of stage performance by <a href=\"/wiki/Tricycle_Theatre\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Tricycle Theatre\">Tricycle Theatre</a> in London.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Bloody_Sunday:_Scenes_from_the_Saville_Inquiry&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20050405182630/http://www.tricycle.co.uk/htmlnew/whatson/show.php3?id=71\">\"Bloody Sunday: Scenes from the Saville Inquiry\"</a>. Tricycle Theatre. 2005. Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.tricycle.co.uk/htmlnew/whatson/show.php3?id=71\">the original</a> on 2005-04-05<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2009-02-19</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Bloody+Sunday%3A+Scenes+from+the+Saville+Inquiry&amp;rft.pub=Tricycle+Theatre&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.tricycle.co.uk%2Fhtmlnew%2Fwhatson%2Fshow.php3%3Fid%3D71&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABloody+Sunday%3A+Scenes+from+the+Saville+Inquiry\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation news\">Liz Hoggard (27 March 2005). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/arts/features/story/0,11710,1446221,00.html\">\"Out of crises, a drama\"</a>. <i>The Guardian</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2009-02-19</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Guardian&amp;rft.atitle=Out+of+crises%2C+a+drama&amp;rft.date=2005-03-27&amp;rft.au=Liz+Hoggard&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Farts%2Ffeatures%2Fstory%2F0%2C11710%2C1446221%2C00.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABloody+Sunday%3A+Scenes+from+the+Saville+Inquiry\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20081001223059/http://www.dublinks.com/index.cfm/loc/14/pt/0/spid/85F418D2-6CD9-4669-8A9FA731AF2AB0CC.htm\">\"Bloody Sunday: Scenes from the Saville Inquiry\"</a>. <i>Dublinks</i>. 2005. Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.dublinks.com/index.cfm/loc/14/pt/0/spid/85F418D2-6CD9-4669-8A9FA731AF2AB0CC.htm\">the original</a> on 2008-10-01<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2009-02-19</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Dublinks&amp;rft.atitle=Bloody+Sunday%3A+Scenes+from+the+Saville+Inquiry&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.dublinks.com%2Findex.cfm%2Floc%2F14%2Fpt%2F0%2Fspid%2F85F418D2-6CD9-4669-8A9FA731AF2AB0CC.htm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABloody+Sunday%3A+Scenes+from+the+Saville+Inquiry\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Further_reading\">Further reading</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a 